thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: All students are humans. If someone studies, then they are a student. A person either studys or teaches. No young person teaches. Jerry neither teaches nor is a manager. Rose is young or a student.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? It is not true that Rose is a student and Jerry is a human.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Student(x) ::: x is a student.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.
Study(x) ::: x studies.
Teach(x) ::: x teaches.
Young(x) ::: x is young.
Manager(x) ::: x is a manager.
Premises:
∀x (Student(x) → Human(x)) ::: All students are humans.
∀x (Study(x) → Student(x)) ::: If someone studies, then they are a student.
∀x (Study(x) ⊕ Teach(x)) ::: A person either studies or teaches.
∀x (Young(x) → ¬Teach(x)) ::: No young person teaches.
¬(Teach(jerry) ∨ Manager(jerry)) ::: Jerry neither teaches nor is a manager.
Young(rose) ∨ Student(rose) ::: Rose is young or a student.
Conclusion:
¬(Student(rose) ∧ Human(jerry)) ::: It is not true that Rose is a student and Jerry is a human.

Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Student(x) ::: x is a student.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.
Study(x) ::: x studies.
Teach(x) ::: x teaches.
Young(x) ::: x is young.
Manager(x) ::: x is a manager.
Premises:
∀x (Student(x) → Human(x)) ::: All students are humans.
∀x (Study(x) → Student(x)) ::: If someone studies, then they are a student.
∀x (Study(x) ⊕ Teach(x)) ::: A person either studies or teaches.
∀x (Young(x) → ¬Teach(x)) ::: No young person teaches.
¬(Teach(jerry) ∨ Manager(jerry)) ::: Jerry neither teaches nor is a manager.
Young(rose) ∨ Student(rose) ::: Rose is young or a student.
Conclusion:
¬(Student(rose) ∧ Human(jerry)) ::: It is not true that Rose is a student and Jerry is a human.
